The virtual cell challenge is a brand new challenge released by the [Arc Institute](https://arcinstitute.org/) to help progress single cell predictions against perturbations. This research is crucial into our understanding of how cells behave under perturbations and allows us to create novel cells. It comes alongside their own release of [State](https://github.com/ArcInstitute/state), a model to do just this.

> Understanding, predicting, and ultimately programming how cells respond to internal cues and external stimuli is a fundamental challenge in biology.

